<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-BA1FBADB-B384-4566-94B0-5A2D78B68783" version="5" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-BA1FBADB-B384-4566-94B0-5A2D78B68783" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">Collect</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M148684-B19"><p class="- topic/p ">In the Collect screen you see all collected machine info, and you can enter the reason for your visit. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-E2C5C008-64D5-41D5-B176-B4FADEB47935" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Example Collect screen</title><fig id="GUID-F15EEC2F-A5EA-4480-828F-04BCAF078AD8" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-271EABAB-78C1-43BA-8E48-1015BF128F7D-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-271EABAB-78C1-43BA-8E48-1015BF128F7D-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="M148684-B20" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Description</title><table id="GUID-3B1F0A75-9EA4-4B40-972E-5072C1457B24" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="30*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="70*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Section 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Machine info 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">This section of the screen shows information about the print system. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Click the Settings &amp; Counters button to view all settings and counters of this system. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See: 
<xref keyref="Adam_config_report" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-621E9C0A-3014-4CBC-BC6A-A005A80FC8CE.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot gentext?>Settings and Counters</xref> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Click the Modifications button to get information on the installed/removed modifications. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See: 
<xref keyref="Adam_modifications" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-8E8D4032-17E2-4614-A5CE-9C7FFCCD2D56.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot gentext?>Modifications</xref> 
</p></li></ul></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Reasons/issues 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Main reason: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">If the product has the option "Installation feedback" enabled, and you have indicated that the visit is an installation visit, then the main reason is already listed as "Installation". 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">For a standard service visit, five main reasons are predefined. One out of these five possible main reasons must be selected. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">See 
<xref keyref="Adam_2nd_visit" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-5E8447EE-B4D2-449F-9CB4-82908437B606.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>Logging a second visit</xref> for more information about a follow-up visit. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">This is a mandatory field. 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">Job reference: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">You can enter your job ticket number for this service visit as provided by your local back office. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">It is also possible that the Job reference field is already filled out via a back-office interface. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">This is an optional field. 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">Issue type: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">After the Main reason is filled out, one or multiple issues may be logged. Each issue needs to be categorized via a list of predefined issue types. The options for issue types can differ per product. For the example screen above: Select one out of nine possible issue types. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">This is a mandatory field. 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">Issue description: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">You can enter additional information to describe in your own words the issue in more detail. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">It is also possible that the Issue description field is already filled out via a back-office interface. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">This is an optional field. 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">Issue: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Click the + icon to add additional issues if your service visit includes multiple issues. 
</p></li></ul></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Previous service session 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Previous session reasons/issues:
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">This section of the screen shows information about the previous service visit. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">A check mark means the issue was solved. A red cross means the issue was not solved. 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks previous session:
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Two types of remarks exist: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks previous visit: This is a remark that was entered during the previous visit. It is presented on the Collect screen as a reminder for this visit. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Recurring remark: This is a remark that will be shown at every service visit until it is updated or removed. An example for Recurring remarks is the indication of customer specific needs or reminders. 
</p></li></ul></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="GUID-F08988EF-EBC8-4C5B-A07D-805BDC1EDF42.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>The ADAM structure</linktext></link><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool "><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="GUID-02A7B545-044B-40A7-BFE4-FE15134FF359.xml" role="child"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Report a printer installation</linktext></link><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="GUID-621E9C0A-3014-4CBC-BC6A-A005A80FC8CE.xml" role="child"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot gentext?>Settings and Counters</linktext></link><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="GUID-8E8D4032-17E2-4614-A5CE-9C7FFCCD2D56.xml" role="child"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot gentext?>Modifications</linktext></link><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="GUID-5E8447EE-B4D2-449F-9CB4-82908437B606.xml" role="child"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Logging a second visit</linktext></link></linkpool></linkpool></related-links>
</concept>